Project 2: Stripline Bandpass Filter (4.0–4.2 GHz)

**Objective:**  
Design a bandpass filter using stripline transmission lines on Rogers RT/Duroid 5880 substrate (2 × 0.031", 1 oz copper).

**Specifications:**
- Passband: 4000–4200 MHz  
- Insertion Loss: < 2.0 dB  
- Attenuation at 3.7 GHz: > 35 dB  
- System Impedance: 50 Ω  
- Minimum Line Width/Gap: > 0.005 inch  

**Implementation Highlights:**
- Stripline structure using SLIN, SSTEP, and other ADS models
- Minimum 1/8" lines at input/output
- EM simulation with Momentum
- Physically realizable layout
